messages.messageBody:
Ha ha, I hope we aren't going there again. LOL. Since you brought it
up I find it rather sexually charged. The doe showing no alarm
within her bower, the overhanging maple. The stag almost rampant at
the entrance almost within the her sanctuary. The symbolism can go
on and on. Not yet needing those powdered unguents, I believe the
magic of the deer is protection from demons. John
